that is, given ğ‘“ defined on a compact set in â„, does there exist ğ‘” which is the form of (1) and equals ğ‘“ 
at given points and approximates ğ‘“ well? We show that it is hard to approximate in the topology of 
ğ¶(ğ¾), but we may put other conditions on ğ‘“ and try to approximate in another topology. Though the 
paper does not give a satisfying result in the case of approximating in the topology of ğ¶(ğ¾), the 
discussion is still constructive. 
